			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=532022">Katta Castellum</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Arbogast & Miller - Cloak of Truth</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Arbogast & Miller - Cloak of Truth</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=537821"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:">Shiznettobam</a> | 
		                        12/26/2001 3:55:08 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">The quest starts in Katta Castellum.  It is started by hailing a cleric npc named Arbogast who should be in the tavern that is down near the bank within the lower part of the city.  He should be standing at a table inside with his friend Miller as well.

After you have hailed him and asked him the right questions, he will give you a flask of holy water to go splash in Phenic Dionicas’ face.  Phenic is one of the head magistrates in Katta Castellum and resides in a huge mansion located near the Tenebrous Mountains zone.  Approach him and give him your flask of holy water given to you by Arbogast.  In return, Phenic will wonder why you splashed water on him and give you some of his drink in replacement.  Return to Arbogast and give him the water received from Phenic.

With this, Arbogast will give you a 2-item container and ask that you retrieve Nathyn Illuminous’ memoirs in order to prove that he is really Tsaph Katta, savior of Katta Castellum.  Nathyn resides in his own little 2-story mansion (everything in Katta is practically a mansion) around the corner of the Tenebrous Mountains zone.  If you hail his guards, they will say Nathyn is a very busy man, but you know it is his house before you enter.  Go into his house and walk up to the 2nd floor.  Look around and find the door that is locked up here.  Find a rogue to pick the lock for you and go inside.  If the book is up on the table in this room, the door will shut and “a coterie servant” will spawn.  This vampyre will be green or light blue to a 60 (fought 2 versions) and easily soloable, even by a rogue.  Kill him and pick up the book from the desk.  The book is the memoirs of Nathyn Illuminous and should be put into the wrapping container that Arbogast gave you.  Combine it in the container by itself and return to Arbogast and give it to him.

After this, Arbogast will tell you that he believes there is no such thing as Norrath, and that he wants proof about the planet and the great Exodus of people from Norrath to Luclin.  He also gives you another wrapping paper container (this is done throughout the quest to prevent people starting on a different step in the quest).  He mentions that if there were such a book, it would be in the great library at Shadowhaven.  Travel to Shadowhaven, go back to the casters guild areas in the back through the cave, and find the library where you can buy Luclin spells.  I went around and hailed all the people here and asking them where I could find a book on the Exodus.  Eventually I found Rianna Birchard.  She told me that the only book was given out to Peqi, and that she hoped the gnome would never return to the library.  I then asked a ranger in the zone if there was a Peqi on tracking, and sure enough, there was.  I found him in one of the slum houses near the cave to the casters’ guilds (can’t remember loc of the house).  I hailed him, but he doesn’t say anything to informative.  I then asked him where the book of the Exodus was.  At this he said he had many books and a book on the Exodus…but they were his, and I wouldn’t get them even over his dead body.  He was a blue con (found out later he’s a very low full blue con to a 60) so I asked a 57-bard friend to help me kill him.  We pulled him to the zone and killed him with ease (I even ASSASSINATED him when he started running).  The 2nd time I took him out I had a 59 wizzy friend with me and took him down with ease yet again.  Lo and behold, he dropped a book on the Exodus.  I combined this in the wrapping paper container, ran back to Katta Castellum, and gave the item to Arbogast.

He gives you another container at this point and accuses the book of being full of lies.  He believes that he convinces you as well, and that you see the truth of it all.  He then wishes for you to go on “an expedition” for him.  He wants you to obtain some items to demystify the truth for the rest of the people.  He asks for you to go to Akheva and obtain two items called “Akuel xi ans vius,” some no rent, marble-looking items dropped from mobs known as “The Protector” in Akheva’s Ruins.

Once you have obtained these, contain them in the wrapping container and return to Arbogast.  At this point, have a group ready (I didn’t know this on the first try) and hand in the combined item to Arbogast.  They mutter how they thought that would kill, but they will go to the bank and get the 2 pieces of a cloak for you.  Both Miller and Arbogast walk over to the bank nearby and stop for a second.  They then despawn/respawn (I think, not totally sure) and attempt to run away.  This is the point that I knew I had to kill them.  Arbogast is a cleric, and Miller is a warrior.  They are both blue cons and can be killed by a group easily…they also are pulled single, or should be.  Once you have killed both of them (you have to kill both as they each have a piece for the resulting item), loot the cloak container from Miller and the neckpiece from Arbogast.  Put the neckpiece in the cloak container and hit combine.  You are now the proud new owner of a Cloak of Truth: ac15 10str 5dex 5cha 8wis Skill mod: Meditate 5% 13.0 wt.

[IMG]http://icdweb.cc.purdue.edu/~reesers/Screenshots/cloakoftruth.jpg[/IMG]
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
